Patch Set 15: Code-Review+2
Change has been successfully merged

I don't think we want to run all these socket connections.  We're not going to want to have Dropbear SSH.

Can you rebase this commit and eliminate all the socket operations?

I suspect we need to add some development to obmc-console to support mux'd operations directly rather than coding it up in a script.

There was also some on-going discussion in the yosemite4 design about UARTs and we might be moving some of these over to a USB-UART device so that this code is maybe not relevant anymore anyhow.

This commit has been rebased and remove the socket operation changes,
thank you for reviewing.
g
Why isn't this using OBMC_CONSOLE_INST directly?  I don't understand why we took OBMC_CONSOLE_INST and then counted them and then did a mapping to a different set of integers?

the content of OBMC_CONSOLE_INST is "1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8", lists the console instances
I count the number of instance into OBMC_CONSOLE_INST_CNT is "8",
then to ensure dynamic getting the UART configs, iterates the instance for each uart channel ttyS0, tty1...etc but skip ttyS4 used by aspeed bmc console itself, so the content of SERVER_CONFS is "file://server.ttyS0.conf file://server.ttyS1.conf file://server.ttyS2.conf file://server.ttyS3.conf file://server.ttyS5.conf file://server.ttyS6.conf file://server.ttyS7.conf file://server.ttyS8.conf"
Aren't these port numbers, which correspond to the dropbear stuff we're trying to drop?  What happens if we don't supply these client conf files?

If I change to SRC_URI:append:fb-compute-multihost = " ${SERVER_CONFS}",
it will impact all former multi-host projects failed with ssh using.

So far, I'll keep 2200~2203 configs, please help to reply if I should remove them all.
Same question here.  Why are we doing this complex mapping work instead of using OBMC_HOST_INSTANCES directly?

The reason is similar to above, the content of HOST_LOGGER_CONFS is "file://ttyS0.conf file://ttyS1.conf file://ttyS2.conf file://ttyS3.conf file://ttyS5.conf file://ttyS6.conf file://ttyS7.conf file://ttyS8.conf"
client conf 2204~2207 has been removed.
